%description:
Regression test for the RFC 5036 Section 2.6 label distribution modes (commit C2):
Downstream Unsolicited distribution, independent control, and liberal retention -- the
new DEFAULTS (Ldp.ned's distributionMode/controlMode/retentionMode) -- in
examples/mpls/ldp (network LDPTEST), reusing the shipped example's own scenario (LSR2
shutdown@2s, startup@10s, examples/mpls/ldp/scenario.xml) run out to its full
sim-time-limit of 11s.

Two-phase scenario, both asserted via a single ordered contains-regex check plus a
whole-run not-contains check:
  1. Normal startup: an unsolicited Label Mapping is advertised (Ldp::duAdvertiseToPeer)
     WITHOUT ever having sent/received a Label Request first -- this is the defining
     behavioral difference from the (old-default, still selectable) DoD request/response
     flow.
  2. The LSR2 shutdown forces a next-hop change for every FEC that used to route through
     it (see ldp_label_withdraw.test's description of the redundant LSR1-LSR4-LSR3 /
     LSR1-LSR5-LSR3 paths). Under liberal retention, the surviving peers had ALREADY been
     flooded a mapping for these FECs earlier (DU advertises to every OPERATIONAL peer,
     not just a FEC's current next hop) -- so the switchover reuses that already-held
     mapping instantly (Ldp::duAdvertiseToPeer's dit-found branch), without ANY new Label
     Request, at any point in the whole run.

Falsification: this test FAILS against the parent commit -- distributionMode/
controlMode/retentionMode do not exist there (this ini's `[Config dod]` section, which
this file only documents -- see ldp_du_mode_dod.test for the config actually exercising
it -- would fail to parse: "unknown parameter"), and the DEFAULT (and only) behavior is
the old DoD request/response flow, so neither the "DU: advertising unsolicited Label
Mapping" line nor the "liberal retention switchover" line exists in the log, and Label
Request lines are pervasive throughout (violating the not-contains check). Verified by
stashing this commit's source changes (keeping this .test file), rebuilding the debug
library, re-running (FAIL: neither contains-regex line is found, and the ini itself
fails ONLY when `-c dod` is passed -- this General-config run fails on the missing
contains-regex lines instead), then restoring the changes and rebuilding again (PASS).

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.ldp.LDPTEST
sim-time-limit = 11s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-event-banners = false
**.LSR*.ldp.cmdenv-log-level = info
**.scenarioManager.cmdenv-log-level = info
**.cmdenv-log-level = off
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-#${runnumber}.sca"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host2"

**.host3.numApps = 1
**.host3.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host3.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host3.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host3.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host3.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host3.app[0].destAddresses = "host4"

**.host{2..4}.numApps = 1
**.host{2..4}.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host{2..4}.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/host4.rt"

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/LSR5.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

**.LSR*.holdTime = 6s
**.LSR*.helloInterval = 2s

**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/ldp/scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# documentation only -- the General config above (this file's only executed run) already
%# IS the distributionMode="du"/controlMode="independent"/retentionMode="liberal" default;
%# this section spells out the legacy combination for a manual `-c dod` repro. opp_test
%# runs exactly one config per .test file (no `-c` here means "General" only), so the
%# actual automated check of this legacy combination lives in the companion file
%# ldp_du_mode_dod.test (%extraargs: -c dod against the identical network/scenario).
[Config dod]
description = "legacy Downstream-on-Demand/ordered/conservative combination (see ldp_du_mode_dod.test)"
**.LSR*.ldp.distributionMode = "dod"
**.LSR*.ldp.controlMode = "ordered"
**.LSR*.ldp.retentionMode = "conservative"

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# phase 1 (normal startup): an unsolicited Label Mapping is sent -- proactively, not in
%# response to a Label Request -- then eventually (phase 2) the LSR2 shutdown fires and a
%# liberal-retention switchover reuses an already-held mapping for the new next hop
%contains-regex: stdout
DU: advertising unsolicited Label Mapping.*processing <shutdown> command\.\.\..*\(liberal retention switchover if the next hop just changed\)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# across the WHOLE run (both phases), no Label Request is EVER received: DU's proactive
%# advertisement (independent control especially) never needs one, unlike the old DoD
%# request/response flow
%not-contains: stdout
Label Request from LSR
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# host traffic is still delivered end-to-end across both phases (cumulative over the
%# whole 11s run, matching ldp_label_withdraw.test/ldp_peer_death.test's convention)
%postrun-command: grep -E "host(2|4)\.app\[0\] packetReceived:count" results/General-#0.sca | awk '$NF > 0 { print "DELIVERED", $0 }' > delivered.out
%contains: delivered.out
DELIVERED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
